The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for biomedical named entity recognition (BioNER), which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of multiple models and collaboration between them, which involves techniques such as transfer learning and ensemble learning, indicating a focus on machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI). Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed approach using precision, recall, and F1 score, which are common evaluation metrics in information retrieval (IR) tasks. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category.
